09/03/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- The World Bank's resident representative to Albania, Nadir Mohammed, said the fight against corruption is the country's main task as it makes the transition to a market economy.
In remarks published Wednesday (9 March) in the local press, Mohammed also stressed the need for intensified efforts towards poverty reduction, infrastructure upgrades and attracting foreign investment.
The World Bank has so far supported 55 development projects in Albania with a total amount of $768m since 1991.
(Albanian News - 09/03/05)
